### [Rio Grande rift](/Rio_Grande_rift)

The [Rio Grande rift](/Rio_Grande_rift) is a geological anomaly, a significant north–south-trending structural basin that bisects the [Rocky Mountains](/Rocky_Mountains) in the [United States](/United States). It’s essentially a vast scar on the Earth’s crust, a testament to the planet’s ongoing, and frankly, rather dramatic, geological adolescence. This rift system stretches for approximately 1,000 kilometers (620 miles), originating in [central Colorado](/Colorado) and extending southward through [New Mexico](/New_Mexico) into [northern Mexico](/Mexico). It’s a feature that demands attention, not out of beauty, but out of sheer, raw geological power.

